title: Grateful Dead Live at Philadelphia Civic Center on 1984-04-21
lineage: Cassette Master (Nakamichi DR-1) > Korg MR-1000 (1-bit/5.6MHz) > Audiogate (1-bit/5.6MHz > 16-bit/44.1KHz) > cdwav (edits)
description:
Set 1

Alabama Getaway-> Promised Land, Friend Of The Devil, Me & My Uncle, Mexicali Blues, West L.A. Fadeaway, Minglewood Blues, Tennessee Jed, Looks Like Rain-> Deal

Set 2

Help On The Way-> Slipknot!-> Franklin's Tower-> Playin' In The Band-> China Doll-> Don't Need Love-> Drums-> Wharf Rat-> Throwing Stones-> Not Fade Away, E: Brokedown Palace

reviews.review_text: Civic Center vs. The Rectum The Civic Center was a beautiful place to see a show compared to the Spectrum, or "The Rectum" as we called it. For some reason this was the only time that The Dead played there, all other times they played at the Spectrum of JFK. These Civic center shows (three of them) were quite good this tour, nothing super special but it was much more intimate than The Rectum was. However, I did see some sick shows at The Rectum. Not sure why they never played the Civic center again, but this show was fairly good for '84.

3rd show Hey now- this was my 3rd show- remember driving with two close friends to the civic center.  Met a kid who was "living" in the parking garage near by.  he had camped out in a service room- we all shared some beers, grilled cheese on his camp stove, and crazy paper....I believe this to be my first show that I "got it".  74 GD shows later and a lot older now.  Thanks for posting this show and helping keep the vibe alive.

THANKS JERRY!!!!!

Overshadowed show 4/20 is an excellent show but don't miss this one. This was my first show, I wasn't prepared for this crowd, but by the next year I would have become one (happily).  This show is raw and exploratory. '84 was hit/miss but the playing had a raw essence to it.  The boys just seemed to go after it not trying to put together a succinct type of rock show but seeing where things might be able to go.  The HSF is a perfect example. Brent going one direction Jerry the other.  They crash into Slipknot and proceed to tear it up.  Wharf Rat is what I took away from my 1st, I think its still one of the tops ever!  Quality stuff in this show give it a spin!
